- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a cloud-based storage system that utilizes server clusters for efficient and reliable data storage. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the integration of erasure coding and data deduplication for storage efficiency. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper discusses the storage and retrieval of large amounts of data. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a prototype storage system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the integration of different configurations for real-time and archival applications.
